    "name": "Mesh Convergence Study for Non-Cannulated Pedicle Screw FEA Model",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was performed on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model. Three mesh densities (coarse ~180k elements, medium ~420k elements, fine ~950k elements) were evaluated. Construct stiffness and peak von Mises stress at the screw-rod junction were monitored as convergence metrics. The Richardson extrapolation method was applied to estimate the discretization error, yielding a grid convergence index (GCI) below 2% for all primary quantities of interest, confirming that the medium mesh density is sufficient for production runs.",
    "activityType": "MeshConvergenceStudy",
